id: pm-9ect
title: "SDK lintExtensionBlueprint + assertExtensionBlueprint: author-time preflight for composeExtension blueprints (capability drift, duplicate commands, empty surfaces)"
description: "Add author-time preflight for declarative blueprints so the two footguns `composeExtension`'s own docstring names are caught at edit/test time instead of at activation:\n\n1. `lintExtensionBlueprint(blueprint, options?): ExtensionBlueprintLintResult` (src/sdk/compose.ts) — pure data analysis, no activation. Structured findings:\n   - `capability_undeclared` (ERROR): a capability the blueprint exercises is missing from the declared set; the loader throws `extension_capability_missing` at activation. The author-time form of that hard failure.\n   - `capability_unused` (WARNING): a declared capability the blueprint never exercises; the runtime equivalent is the `pm package doctor` `extension_capability_unused` advisory (pm-fk84). This makes lintExtensionBlueprint the author-time inverse of `reconcileExtensionCapabilityUsage`, just as `deriveExtensionCapabilities` is for the used set.\n   - `duplicate_command` (WARNING): the same normalized command path declared twice in `commands` (silent last-wins shadow at dispatch).\n   - `command_override_conflict` (WARNING): a path declared as both a fresh `commands` definition and a `commandOverrides` override (contradictory).\n   - `empty_surface` (WARNING): a registration field present but empty (e.g. `commands: []`) — a dead declaration.\n   - `manifest_capabilities_absent` (WARNING): blueprint exercises capabilities but provides no declared set to reconcile against; suggests `capabilities: deriveExtensionCapabilities(blueprint)`.\n   Declared set comes from `options.declaredCapabilities` or `blueprint.manifest.capabilities`, normalized through the same `normalizeKnownExtensionCapability` (legacy-alias aware) the runtime reconciler uses.\n\n2. `assertExtensionBlueprint(blueprint, options?)` (src/sdk/testing.ts) — the assert* family member: runs the linter and throws (plain Error, matching the file convention) on any error-severity finding, returning the lint result on success so a test can still inspect warnings. One-liner CI guard for package authors.\n\nScope: SDK barrel + /sdk/testing re-export, docs/SDK.md (Declarative Authoring + Testing Helpers), 100% test + docstring coverage. Lives author-time/test-only (a blueprint is in-code data, not on disk), consistent with the assert*/run* family."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: "area:extensions","area:sdk",pm-cli
