learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-22T22:00:59.049Z",claude-code-agent,"lintExtensionBlueprint must resolve legacy capability aliases (migration/validation -> schema) on the author's declared set, even though the runtime reconcileExtensionCapabilityUsage only uses normalizeKnownExtensionCapability. Reason: the loader runs normalizeManifestCapabilities (which alias-resolves) BEFORE reconciliation, so by reconcile-time aliases are already canonical; but the author-time lint sees the RAW manifest.capabilities, so it must resolve aliases itself (resolveLegacyExtensionCapabilityAlias ?? normalizeKnownExtensionCapability) or it would emit a false-positive capability_undeclared error for a manifest that actually loads fine. Unknown capabilities are dropped (a separate diagnostic owns them) so a typo is not misreported as unused. capability_undeclared is the only ERROR severity (loader throws); everything else is advisory WARNING so ok stays true."
